<dl id="n42030d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42030d">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42030d"> 30(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sir &amp; very dear / friend</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The fame of his labours in the cause of Temperance reached the Pope, and through an aspiring priest who visited Rome about that period, the Pope&apos;s Blessing was sent to Mr. Chiniquy, as testified by the following letter. &hellip; &ldquo;Sir and very Dear Friend: &hellip; <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) vi</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09138c" href="c09all.htm#c09138c">VI.C.09:138(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
